I"<p>When I read a book to learn I try read it more then once. It take multiple passes and multiple formats to learn material.</p>

<p>My methodology is this:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Read the book and highlight sections the are interesting or important.</li>
  <li>After short period of time read it again taking notes.</li>
  <li>Curate notes by removing or adding sections and updating the text. If a section is confusing or remains unclear, I refer back to the book and review it, updating my notes accordingly.</li>
  <li>If the book contains examples. tutorials or practice problems then go back and do them. (Sometimes.)</li>
  <li>Review the notes from time to time.</li>
</ol>

<p>There is not enough hours in the day to do this for every book I read, but it is a habit I try to keep.</p>
